{"tid":2297802,"cid":5,"subCid":11,"title":"大律師公會投訴《大公報》報道接近藐視法庭　去信鄭若驊籲跟進捍衛司法制度","createTime":"2020-11-23T14:15:21.000Z","updateTime":"2020-11-24T02:27:32.000Z","uid":240362,"like":45,"dislike":5,"uniUserReply":32,"replies":[{"pid":"ef04b0ccbcc036650f9efefa50414b494f3191ae","tid":2297802,"uid":240362,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-11-23T14:15:21.000Z","msg":"高等法院法官周家明本月19日裁定，警方去年示威活動執法不展示警員編號違《人權法》。香港大律師公會今（23日）去信律政司長鄭若驊，投訴《大公報》本月20日的相關報道攻擊周家明，徘徊藐視法庭的邊緣，呼籲鄭若驊堅決捍衛司法制度和法官的獨立性，對抗報道的惡意指控，嚴肅看待此事並採取適當行動。<br />\n<br />\n《大公報》當日一篇標題為〈暴徒惡晒 警察冇人權-警員不展示編號 高院裁違人權法〉的報道，製圖中一名示威者在警察前手持汽油彈說：「我有法官撐我，快啲畀個編號我睇！」。大律師公會指出，報道傳達周官偏袒示威者，或支持犯罪活動的信息，報道中亦有人對法官作人身攻擊，質疑法官的動機和誠信。<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n大律師公會認為《大公報》報道已超出批評司法決定的可接受範圍，已接近構成藐視法庭，根據高法官高浩文早前指出，律政司有責任就針對法官及司法機構的不正確指控辯護，並重申公眾對法官作無根據的人身攻擊是不可接受，損害司法公正和法治。<br />\n<br />\n大律師公會今亦發聲明表示，有傳媒及個別人物就判決對法官周家明作出抨擊，對此感到痛心，強烈譴責針對司法機構及司法人員所作出的非理性與克制的攻擊行為。<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://news.mingpao.com/ins/%E6%B8%AF%E8%81%9E/article/20201123/s00001/1606118301148/%E6%B3%95%E5%AE%98%E5%91%A8%E5%AE%B6%E6%98%8E%E8%A2%AB%E6%94%BB%E6%93%8A-%E5%A4%A7%E5%BE%8B%E5%B8%AB%E5%85%AC%E6%9C%83%E6%8A%95%E8%A8%B4%E3%80%8A%E5%A4%A7%E5%85%AC%E5%A0%B1%E3%80%8B%E5%A0%B1%E9%81%93%E6%8E%A5%E8%BF%91%E8%97%90%E8%A6%96%E6%B3%95%E5%BA%AD-%E5%8E%BB%E4%BF%A1%E9%84%AD%E8%8B%A5%E9%A9%8A%E7%B1%B2%E8%B7%9F%E9%80%B2%E6%8D%8D%E8%A1%9B%E5%8F%B8%E6%B3%95%E5%88%B6%E5%BA%A6\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fnews.mingpao.com%2Fins%2F%25E6%25B8%25AF%25E8%2581%259E%2Farticle%2F20201123%2Fs00001%2F1606118301148%2F%25E6%25B3%2595%25E5%25AE%2598%25E5%2591%25A8%25E5%25AE%25B6%25E6%2598%258E%25E8%25A2%25AB%25E6%2594%25BB%25E6%2593%258A-%25E5%25A4%25A7%25E5%25BE%258B%25E5%25B8%25AB%25E5%2585%25AC%25E6%259C%2583%25E6%258A%2595%25E8%25A8%25B4%25E3%2580%258A%25E5%25A4%25A7%25E5%2585%25AC%25E5%25A0%25B1%25E3%2580%258B%25E5%25A0%25B1%25E9%2581%2593%25E6%258E%25A5%25E8%25BF%2591%25E8%2597%2590%25E8%25A6%2596%25E6%25B3%2595%25E5%25BA%25AD-%25E5%258E%25BB%25E4%25BF%25A1%25E9%2584%25AD%25E8%258B%25A5%25E9%25A9%258A%25E7%25B1%25B2%25E8%25B7%259F%25E9%2580%25B2%25E6%258D%258D%25E8%25A1%259B%25E5%258F%25B8%25E6%25B3%2595%25E5%2588%25B6%25E5%25BA%25A6&d=4eD5kuUGVNxCcHpGsLYUnf3ZlJXgeXtiTXALECG4O5Q%3D&h=cf33d8b2\" data-ef-url=\"https://embed.lih.kg/frame?u=https%3A%2F%2Fnews.mingpao.com%2Fins%2F%25E6%25B8%25AF%25E8%2581%259E%2Farticle%2F20201123%2Fs00001%2F1606118301148%2F%25E6%25B3%2595%25E5%25AE%2598%25E5%2591%25A8%25E5%25AE%25B6%25E6%2598%258E%25E8%25A2%25AB%25E6%2594%25BB%25E6%2593%258A-%25E5%25A4%25A7%25E5%25BE%258B%25E5%25B8%25AB%25E5%2585%25AC%25E6%259C%2583%25E6%258A%2595%25E8%25A8%25B4%25E3%2580%258A%25E5%25A4%25A7%25E5%2585%25AC%25E5%25A0%25B1%25E3%2580%258B%25E5%25A0%25B1%25E9%2581%2593%25E6%258E%25A5%25E8%25BF%2591%25E8%2597%2590%25E8%25A6%2596%25E6%25B3%2595%25E5%25BA%25AD-%25E5%258E%25BB%25E4%25BF%25A1%25E9%2584%25AD%25E8%258B%25A5%25E9%25A9%258A%25E7%25B1%25B2%25E8%25B7%259F%25E9%2580%25B2%25E6%258D%258D%25E8%25A1%259B%25E5%258F%25B8%25E6%25B3%2595%25E5%2588%25B6%25E5%25BA%25A6&h=6f547add\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://news.mingpao.com/ins/%E6%B8%AF%E8%81%9E/article/20201123/s00001/1606118301148/%E6%B3%95%E5%AE%98%E5%91%A8%E5%AE%B6%E6%98%8E%E8%A2%AB%E6%94%BB%E6%93%8A-%E5%A4%A7%E5%BE%8B%E5%B8%AB%E5%85%AC%E6%9C%83%E6%8A%95%E8%A8%B4%E3%80%8A%E5%A4%A7%E5%85%AC%E5%A0%B1%E3%80%8B%E5%A0%B1%E9%81%93%E6%8E%A5%E8%BF%91%E8%97%90%E8%A6%96%E6%B3%95%E5%BA%AD-%E5%8E%BB%E4%BF%A1%E9%84%AD%E8%8B%A5%E9%A9%8A%E7%B1%B2%E8%B7%9F%E9%80%B2%E6%8D%8D%E8%A1%9B%E5%8F%B8%E6%B3%95%E5%88%B6%E5%BA%A6</a>"},{"pid":"64022146519095110553ce20a947131125adcffa","tid":2297802,"uid":240362,"like":4,"dislike":0,"score":4,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-11-23T14:15:55.000Z","msg":"The Hong Kong Bar Association (HKBA) has demanded that Justice Secretary Teresa Cheng take action against pro-Beijing newspaper Ta Kung Pao over its attack on a High Court judge who last week ruled against the police practice of riot officers not displaying their ID numbers at protests.<br />\n<br />\nThe association on Monday published a letter it had sent to Cheng expressing its &quot;utter dismay and astonishment&quot; at the way the newspaper reported on the ruling.<br />\n<br />\nThe HKBA noted that a front page headline on Friday read &quot;Thugs rule, no human rights for policemen&quot; and was accompanied by a cartoon depicting a protester saying to an officer &quot;Show me your number, the judge backs me&quot;.<br />\n<br />\nThe association said the article conveyed a message that judge Anderson Chow was partisan and biased in favour of protesters, or that he supported criminal activities.<br />\n<br />\n&quot;The [Bar] Council considers that Ta Kung Pao has gone beyond the boundary of acceptable criticism of judicial decisions,&quot; the letter said, adding that the article &quot;hovers on the margins of a contempt of court&quot;.<br />\n<br />\nThe HKBA reminded Cheng that as justice secretary, it falls to her to defend judges and the judiciary against &quot;the pernicious accusations made in the newspaper article,&quot; and urged her to &quot;take appropriate action&quot;.<br />\n<br />\nMeanwhile, the association also issued a statement warning that individuals who criticised Chow and questioned his motives and integrity could have breached the law.<br />\n<br />\n&quot;Members of the public have the right to discuss and criticise judicial decisions through rational discourse and debate. There is, however, no justification whatsoever for exerting pressure on judges in an attempt to persuade them to decide cases one way or another,&quot; the statement said.<br />\n<br />\n&quot;Depending on the circumstances, this kind of pressure constitutes an interference with judicial proceedings and may be a contempt of court.&quot;<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://news.rthk.hk/rthk/en/component/k2/1561440-20201123.htm?s=09\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fnews.rthk.hk%2Frthk%2Fen%2Fcomponent%2Fk2%2F1561440-20201123.htm%3Fs%3D09&d=4eD5kuUGVNxCcHpGsLYUnf3ZlJXgeXtiTXALECG4O5Q%3D&h=a24f6210\" data-ef-url=\"https://embed.lih.kg/frame?u=https%3A%2F%2Fnews.rthk.hk%2Frthk%2Fen%2Fcomponent%2Fk2%2F1561440-20201123.htm%3Fs%3D09&h=6b4f4042\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://news.rthk.hk/rthk/en/component/k2/1561440-20201123.htm?s=09</a>"},{"pid":"c014356b985dfba8be39ef4d864f567e8a1d12ab","tid":2297802,"uid":76804,"like":11,"dislike":0,"score":11,"citedBy":3,"replyTime":"2020-11-23T14:16:33.000Z","msg":"點解唔show編號可以仲大條道理<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/clown.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/clown.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"c6bfe1d6c5dbb79163c52fbd67191215a14e8916","tid":2297802,"uid":51271,"like":11,"dislike":3,"score":8,"citedBy":2,"replyTime":"2020-11-23T14:16:37.000Z","msg":"你一係就告鳩太公文匯啦，講咁多廢話"},{"pid":"60bd3c75ae06bac353bf4bbf8b81a6a1f9f9aac3","tid":2297802,"uid":251732,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-11-23T14:16:38.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"/assets/faces/lm2/dllm.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/lm2/dllm.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/lm2/dllm.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/lm2/dllm.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"d3e8819be39eb6356be4dc96332e7ad96c6d18ec","tid":2297802,"uid":335434,"like":9,"dislike":0,"score":9,"quote":{"pid":"c6bfe1d6c5dbb79163c52fbd67191215a14e8916","tid":2297802,"uid":51271,"like":11,"dislike":3,"score":8,"citedBy":2,"replyTime":"2020-11-23T14:16:37.000Z","msg":"你一係就告鳩太公文匯啦，講咁多廢話"},"citedBy":2,"replyTime":"2020-11-23T14:18:31.000Z","msg":"大律師公會可以點告人藐視法庭 私人檢控然後等大波驊介入?<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"f703f15266c777b2b122f55228df57b7827ff5c2","tid":2297802,"uid":240362,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"60bd3c75ae06bac353bf4bbf8b81a6a1f9f9aac3","tid":2297802,"uid":251732,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-11-23T14:16:38.000Z","msg":"<img sr